1
00:00:00,087 --> 00:00:03,562
Functions in JavaScript can be expressed in numerous ways

2
00:00:03,800 --> 00:00:07,662
with arrow functions being one of the most concise and modern formats

3
00:00:08,037 --> 00:00:09,850
Introduced in ES6

4
00:00:10,213 --> 00:00:13,050
arrow functions allow for a shorter syntax

5
00:00:13,450 --> 00:00:16,800
especially when dealing with single-return expression functions

6
00:00:17,175 --> 00:00:19,312
Unlike traditional function expressions

7
00:00:19,688 --> 00:00:23,962
arrow functions also handle the context of 'this' differently

8
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,538
which can be particularly beneficial in certain scenarios

